class Solution {
    public long mostPoints(int[][] questions) {
        int n = questions.length;
        long[] dp = new long[n + 1];
        for (int i = n - 1; i >= 0; i--) {
            int points = questions[i][0];
            int brainpower = questions[i][1];
            int next = Math.min(i + brainpower + 1, n);
            dp[i] = Math.max(dp[i + 1], points + dp[next]);
        }
        return dp[0];
    }
}
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(n)
space complexity: O(n)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Dynamic programming is used to track the maximum points that can be earned from the current question onwards. The dp array is filled in reverse order, considering whether to solve or skip each question, and choosing the option that yields the maximum points.
